'''Rodrigo Bentancur Colman''' (born 25 June 1997) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{English football updater|TottenhH}} club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

Bentancur started his career in the youth system of Argentine side [[Boca Juniors]] in 2009. He was promoted to the senior squad in 2015, winning two [[Argentine Primera División|Primera División]] titles and a [[Copa Argentina]] with the team. He was then signed by Italian club [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in 2017, where he won three consecutive [[Serie A]] titles, among other trophies. In January 2022, Bentancur joined English side Tottenham Hotspur, winning the [[2025 UEFA Europa League final|UEFA Europa League]] three and a half seasons later.

At international level, Bentancur was a member of the [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay U20 squad]] that won the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]]. He made his senior debut for Uruguay in 2017, representing the side at the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]], and the [[Copa América]] in [[2019 Copa América|2019]], [[2021 Copa América|2021]] and [[2024 Copa América|2024]].

== Early life ==
Bentancur was born on 25 June 1997 in [[Nueva Helvecia|Nueva Helvecia, Colonia]] to Roberto Bentancur and Mary Colmán. He has a younger brother, Damián, and was nicknamed ''Lolo'' growing up as Damián couldn't pronounce Rodrigo as a child. Bentancur is of [[Irish Uruguayans|Irish]], [[Spanish Uruguayans|Spanish]], and [[Swiss Uruguayans|Swiss]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hendrix |first=Hale |date=22 February 2022 |title=Rodrigo Bentancur Childhood Story Plus Untold Biography Facts |url=https://lifebogger.com/rodrigo-bentancur-childhood-biography-story-facts/ |access-date=2023-11-30 |website=LifeBogger |language=en-US}}</ref>
[[File:Rodrigo Bentancur.jpg|thumb|329x329px|Bentancur training with [[Boca Juniors]] in 2016]]
When Bentancur was four years of age, his mother died of an undisclosed illness. Thereafter, he wore the number 30 shirt in her honour; an homage of her birthday. Roberto eventually remarried to Cecilia Agredi, an [[Argentines in Uruguay|Argentine]] of [[Italian Argentines|Italian]] descent. Together, the two bore female twins, Cande and Mica, Rodrigo and Damián's half-sisters.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Señorans |first=Jorge |title=Rodrigo Bentancur, el niño que le ganó el partido a la vida |url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/rodrigo-bentancur-el-nino-que-le-gano-el-partido-a-la-vida-2018611500 |access-date=2023-11-30 |website=El Observador}}</ref>

Passionate about football since childhood, Bentancur eventually enrolled in [[Boca Juniors]] youth academy in 2009 after Horacio Anselmi, a longtime representative for the club, scouted him.<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 October 2022 |title=Rodrigo Bentancur, el joven que juega con la Celeste en el alma y el número 30 en el corazón |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/uruguay/nota/_/id/10943826/rodrigo-bentancur-perfil-seleccion-uruguaya-boca-juventus-tottenham |access-date=2023-11-30 |website=ESPNdeportes.com |language=es}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Boca Juniors===
On 12 April 2015, he made his first team debut for the Boca Juniors in a league game against [[Club Atlético Nueva Chicago|Nueva Chicago]]. He replaced [[Pablo Pérez (footballer, born 1985)|Pablo Pérez]] after 77 minutes in a 0–0 home draw.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/04/12/argentina/primera-division/boca-juniors/ca-nueva-chicago/1978271/|title=Boca Juniors vs. Nueva Chicago – 12 April 2015 – Soccerway|publisher=Soccerway|date=12 April 2015|access-date=28 June 2015}}</ref> His stint at Boca is mainly remembered<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.historiadeboca.com.ar/jugadores/rodrigo-bentancur/1184/2015/2015/5.html | title=Rodrigo Bentancur – Trayectoria y Biografía de Jugadores – Historia de Boca Juniors }}</ref> for his significant mistake against [[Club Atlético San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]], when he passed the ball to a rival forward ([[Mauro Matos]]) who then easily scored a last-minute victory goal that put his team at the top of the league, above Boca (in spite of this, they ended up winning the [[2015 Argentine Primera División]]).<ref>{{cite web | last=Fuentes | first=Andres | title=Surgió de Boca, ahora lo quieren el Real Madrid y otros dos grandes europeos | website=El Futbolero Argentina | date=11 December 2022 | url=https://www.elfutbolero.com.ar/ligaprofesional/Surgio-de-Boca-ahora-lo-quieren-el-Real-Madrid-y-otros-dos-grandes-europeos-20221211-0028.html | language=es | access-date=8 May 2024}}</ref> He would make a similar mistake some years later, this time playing for Juventus, with a back-pass blunder inside his own penalty area which put his team one nil down in the first seconds of the game, in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League]] Round of 16 (they ended up being eliminated due to the away goals rule).<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.infobae.com/america/deportes/2021/02/17/el-grosero-error-de-bentancur-que-posibilito-el-gol-del-porto-ante-juventus-el-mal-recuerdo-que-les-trajo-a-los-hinchas-de-boca/ | title=El grosero error de Bentancur que posibilitó el gol del Porto ante Juventus: El mal recuerdo que les trajo a los hinchas de Boca | date=17 February 2021 }}</ref>

On 13 July 2015, Bentancur, [[Guido Vadalá]], [[Franco Cristaldo]] and [[Adrián Cubas]] became part of [[Carlos Tevez]]'s deal, which saw [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] have the first option to sign the youngsters until 20 April 2017, with Vadalá also joining Juventus on loan for the 2015–2017 seasons. Bentancur was tagged for €9.4&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/media/native/investor-relations-docs/english/price-sensitive-press-releases/2015-2016/comunicato%2013072015%20accordi%20boca%20eng.pdf|title=Agreements with Boca Juniors|date=13 July 2015|access-date=15 August 2016|publisher=Juventus F.C.|archive-date=27 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127171710/http://www.juventus.com/media/native/investor-relations-docs/english/price-sensitive-press-releases/2015-2016/comunicato%2013072015%20accordi%20boca%20eng.pdf|url-status=dead}}</ref> Juventus's CEO [[Giuseppe Marotta]] later confirmed that Juventus would be exercising their option to sign Bentancur in 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/3923/italy/2016/12/19/30652472/were-working-on-signing-witsel-juventus-ceo-reveals-talks|title=Signing with Bentnacur|date=19 December 2016|access-date=19 December 2016|work=Goal (website)}}</ref> He arrived in Turin on 3 April 2017{{citation needed|date=April 2017}} and completed his medical on the same day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/-bentancur-completes-juventus-medical-.php|title=Bentancur completes Juventus medical|date=3 April 2017|access-date=4 April 2017|publisher=Juventus F.C.}}</ref> On 21 April 2017 Juventus completed their acquisition of Bentancur, signing him on a five-year deal effective from 1 July 2017 until 30 June 2022 for a €9.5&nbsp;million transfer fee, plus additional performance based bonuses. Boca Juniors are also entitled to 50% of any future transfer fee that Juventus receive for Bentancur.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/rodrigo-bentancur-joins-juventus.php|title=Bentancur joins Juventus!|date=21 April 2017|access-date=21 April 2017|publisher=Juventus F.C.}}</ref> Bentancur subsequently returned to Argentina to play out the remainder of the 2016–17 season with Boca Juniors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/serie-a/2016-2017/juventus-announce-signing-of-rodrigo-bentancur_sto6137863/story.shtml|title=Juventus announce signing of Rodrigo Bentancur|publisher=Eurosport.co.uk|author1=Pete Sharland|date=21 April 2017|access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref>

===Juventus===
[[File:Bentancur-juventus-2019 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Bentancur playing for [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in 2019]]
Bentancur formally became a player of Juventus on 1 July 2017, after the club activated the option to sign him in April 2017, in a deal which would keep him at the club until 2022. The first option to sign Bentancur was bought as part of [[Carlos Tevez]]'s deal in July 2015.<ref name="Bentancur joins Juventus">{{cite web|title=Bentancur joins Juventus!|url=http://www.juventus.com/en/news/news/2017/rodrigo-bentancur-joins-juventus.php|publisher=juventus.com|access-date=27 August 2017|date=21 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2017/04/03/football/1491228433_071528.html|title=Juventus announce signing of Rodrigo Bentancur from Boca|author1=Mirko Calemme|work=AS.com |date=3 April 2017|access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> He made his club debut on 26 August 2017, coming on as a substitute in a 4–2 away win over [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]] in [[Serie A]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.sports.yahoo.com/a/36853132/genoa-2-juventus-4-dybala-hits-hat-trick-as-bianconeri-come-back-from-two-down/|title=Paulo Dybala hat-trick helps Juventus overcome sticky Genoa challenge|publisher=Yahoo! Sports|date=27 August 2017|access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41062113|title=Genoa 2–4 Juventus|publisher=BBC|date=26 August 2017|access-date=27 August 2017}}</ref> On 6 October 2018, Bentancur scored his first goal for the club in a 2–0 away win over [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] in [[2018–19 Serie A|Serie A]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/128987/bentancur-enjoys-debut-juve-goal |title=Bentancur enjoys debut Juve goal |publisher=Football Italia |date=6 October 2018 |access-date=6 October 2018 }}</ref> During his time with the club, Italian newspapers nicknamed him as ''Principe.''

===Tottenham Hotspur===
On 31 January 2022, Bentancur joined [[Premier League]] club [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2022/january/bentancur-completes-move/|title=Bentancur completes move|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |accessdate=2 March 2022 |date=31 January 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/en/news/articles/suerte-rodri|title=Suerte, Rodri!|website=juventus.com/en|date=31 January 2022 |accessdate=2 March 2022}}</ref> Bentancur made his debut for Spurs on 5 February in the [[2021–22 FA Cup|FA Cup]] match against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], coming on as a substitute in the match that finished in a 3–1 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2022/02/05/tottenham-hotspur-vs-brighton-fa-cup-live-score-latest-updates/ |title=Space invader Dejan Kulusevski ups the ante at Tottenham with a sureness of touch |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220207125439/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2022/02/05/tottenham-hotspur-vs-brighton-fa-cup-live-score-latest-updates/ |archive-date=7 February 2022 |work=The Daily Telegraph |first= Ivan|last= Speck }}</ref> He made his Premier League debut nine days later, coming on as a substitute for [[Pierre-Emile Højbjerg]] in a 2–3 loss against [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite tweet |publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C. |author-link=Tottenham Hotspur |user=SpursOfficial |number=1491517443520532481 |date=9 February 2022 |title=A Premier League debut for Rodrigo Bentancur. 👏 ➡️ Bentancur ⬅️ Højbjerg ⚪️ 1–1 🟡 (58') https://t.co/T1wLO8Z38u |language=en |access-date=2 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220209210101/https://twitter.com/SpursOfficial/status/1491517443520532481 |archive-date=9 February 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 18 September 2022, Bentancur scored his first goal for the club in a [[Premier League]] game against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], the third goal in a 6–2 victory at the [[Tottenham Hotspur Stadium]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Tottenham 6–2 Leicester: Heung-min Son ends drought with second half hat-trick |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/12698875/tottenham-6-2-leicester-heung-min-son-ends-drought-with-second-half-hat-trick |access-date=29 October 2022 |website=Sky Sports |language=en}}</ref> Later on in the season, Bentancur scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in a group stage match – an equaliser against [[Sporting CP]]. The match ended 1–1. He continued his goal-scoring form in Spurs' league fixture three days later, coming off the bench to score an injury-time winner against [[AFC Bournemouth]], completing a 3–2 comeback after they had gone 2–0 down.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Bentancur scores late winner as Spurs fight back |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63354914 |access-date=29 October 2022}}</ref> Two weeks later he registered his first brace in the Premier League, with two late goals against Leeds United to secure a 4–3 victory for Spurs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/news/2022/november/story-of-the-match-spurs-4-3-leeds-united/|title=Spurs 4–3 Leeds United|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|date=12 November 2022}}</ref>
[[File:Lorencio.jpg|thumb|Bentancur playing for [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] in 2022]]
On 11 February 2023, Bentancur suffered an [[anterior cruciate ligament injury]] during a match against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]], which would rule him out of the team for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/feb/12/rodrigo-bentancur-tottenham-out-for-rest-of-season-injury |title=Rodrigo Bentancur out for rest of season in major blow to Tottenham |first=Fabrizio|last= Romano|date= 12 February 2023|work=The Guardian }}</ref>

Bentancur eventually made his return on 27 October 2023, coming off the bench late in a 1–2 away win against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]] in game week 10. However, just a month after his return, on 26 November during a 1–2 defeat against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], Bentancur tore his ankle ligaments.<ref>{{Cite web |last=sebastianemanuel5 |date=28 November 2023 |title=Breaking: Rodrigo Bentancur out with torn ankle ligaments |url=https://cartilagefreecaptain.sbnation.com/2023/11/28/23979656/breaking-rodrigo-bentancur-out-with-torn-ankle-ligaments |access-date=2023-11-30 |website=Cartilage Free Captain |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Gold |first=Alasdair |date=28 November 2023 |title=Rodrigo Bentancur injury update leaves Postecoglou with big January problems |url=https://www.football.london/tottenham-hotspur-fc/players/rodrigo-bentancur-injury-update-leaves-28191944 |access-date=2023-11-30 |website=Football London |language=en}}</ref> Despite being ruled out for 8 to 10 weeks, Bentancur returned against Bournemouth on 31 December 2023, a little over four weeks later. Bentancur captained the side for the first time in a 1–0 [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]] win over [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on 5 January 2024 and he scored his first goal since his return from injury on 15 January 2024, Tottenham's second equaliser in a 2–2 draw away to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Tottenham fight back to earn draw at Man Utd |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67904868 |access-date=2024-01-15 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> In November 2024, he received a seven-game suspension and imposed with a fine of £100,000 by the [[The Football Association|English FA]] for allegedly making a racist comment toward his teammate [[Son Heung-min]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Hughes |first=Matt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/nov/13/bentancur-set-for-lengthy-ban-over-alleged-racist-remark-about-teammate |title=Bentancur set for lengthy ban over alleged racist remark about teammate |work=The Guardian |date=13 November 2024 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=18 November 2024 |title=Bentancur banned 7 games, fined £100k for racist remark about Spurs teammate Son |url=https://www.scmp.com/sport/football/article/3287092/rodrigo-bentancur-banned-7-matches-after-racist-remark-about-spurs-teammate-son-heung-min |access-date=2024-11-20 |website=South China Morning Post |language=en}}</ref>

On 21 May 2025, he was a member of the Tottenham Hotspur squad that won the UEFA Europa League for the third time in the club's history, defeating Manchester United in the 2025 final.<ref name=":0" />

On 3 October 2025, Bentancur signed a new long-term contract with Tottenham Hotspur.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cvgrdj975wdo| title=Tottenham midfielder Bentancur signs new contract| publisher=BBC SPORT| date=3 October 2025| access-date=7 October 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Bentancur was a member of [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay national under-20 team]], winning the [[2017 South American U-20 Championship]]<ref name=rodspur>{{cite web|url=https://www.tottenhamhotspur.com/teams/men/players/rodrigo-bentancur/|title=Rodrigo Bentancur Profile Statistics & Latest News|access-date=18 January 2024|publisher=Tottenham Hotspur F.C.}}</ref> and finishing fourth at the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/mens/worldcup/2018russia/news/jun-21-rodrigo-bentancur-follow-up-2963894|title=Bentancur: the young talent of a consistent Uruguay|date=21 June 2018|access-date=18 January 2024|publisher=FIFA}}</ref>

In September 2017, Bentancur received his first senior call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]] by manager [[Óscar Tabárez]] for the team's upcoming [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-italia.net/109941/bentancur-gets-uruguay-call|title=Bentancur gets Uruguay call|publisher=Football Italia|date=16 September 2017|access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref> He made his international debut on 5 October, coming on as a substitute in Uruguay's 0–0 away draw against Venezuela.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/serie-a/juventus/2017/10/07-31916695/juventus_bentancur_promosso_anche_da_tabarez/|title=Juventus, Bentancur promosso anche da Tabarez|publisher=Tutto Sport|language=it|author1=Stefano Lanzo|date=7 October 2017|access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/10/05/south-america/wc-qualifying-south-america/venezuela/uruguay/2161506/|title=Venezuela vs. Uruguay 0 – 0|publisher=Soccerway|date=5 October 2017|access-date=13 October 2017}}</ref> He was named in the squad for the [[2018 China Cup|China Cup]] in March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.getfootballnewsitaly.com/2018/torreira-earns-first-uruguayan-call-up/|title=Torreira earns first Uruguayan call-up|website=getfootballnewsitaly.com|publisher=Get Italian Football News|date=4 March 2018|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>

In May 2018, Bentancur was named in Uruguay's provisional 26-man [[Uruguay national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced?|work=Goal (website)|last=Crawford|first=Stephen|date=16 May 2018}}</ref> He was later included in the team's final 23-man squad for the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldsoccer.com/world-cup/uruguay-world-cup-fixtures-399702 |title=Uruguay World Cup Fixtures, Squad, Group, Guide |publisher=World Soccer |author1=Sam Tremlett |date=15 June 2018 |access-date=15 June 2018 }}</ref> He appeared in Uruguay's opening match of the tournament on 15 June, a 1–0 victory over [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] at the [[Yekaterinburg Arena]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/world-cup/2018/06/15/world-cup-2018-egypt-vs-uruguay-live-score-latest-updates/ |title=World Cup 2018: Jose Gimenez grabs late winner for Uruguay to break Egyptian hearts – live reaction |newspaper=The Telegraph |author1=JJ Bull |date=15 June 2018 |access-date=15 June 2018 }}</ref> In the Round of 16 match against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 30 June, he set-up [[Edinson Cavani]]'s second goal in an eventual 2–1 victory.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44439361#tab-2 |title=Uruguay 2–1 Portugal |work=BBC Sport |author1=Gary Rose |date=30 June 2018 |access-date=10 July 2018 }}</ref> Uruguay were eliminated from the tournament following a 2–0 defeat to eventual champions [[France national football team|France]] in the quarter-finals on 6 July.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bevan |first1=Chris |title=Uruguay 0 France 2 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44652179 |work=BBC Sport |access-date=6 July 2018 |location=Nizhny Novgorod |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>

Bentancur was a member of Uruguay's squads for both the 2019 and 2021 [[Copa América|Copas Américas]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://copaamerica2019.live/uruguay-team-squads/ |title=Uruguay Team Squads Copa America 2019 |work=copaamerica2019.live |date=7 March 2019 |access-date=13 June 2019 }}</ref> The team reached the quarter-finals on both occasions, being eliminated by [[Peru national football team|Peru]] and [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] respectively, both in [[penalty shootout]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48777158 |title=Uruguay 0–0 Peru |work=BBC Sport |date=29 June 2019 |access-date=30 June 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/copa-america/uruguay-vs-colombia/cronica/2021/07/04/60e176f722601d61688b466d.html|title=Ospina is the hero as Colombia reach the semis on penalties|date=4 July 2021|access-date=18 January 2024|website=Marca|location=Spain}}</ref>

On 2 February 2022, Bentancur scored his first goal for Uruguay in a 4–1 win over Venezuela in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifier]].<ref name=rodspur/>

In November of the same year, he was named in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Group H#Uruguay|final squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] held in [[Qatar]]. He started all three [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group H|Group H]] matches for ''La Celeste'' but was substituted with an injury in the final fixture against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]].<ref name=rodspur/> Uruguay won the match 2–0 but were eliminated as [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] beat [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] to go through to the round of 16 at Uruguay's expense.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/ghana-uruguay-anrew-ayew-darwin-nunez-sergio-rochet-fifa-world-cup-qatar-2022|title=Uruguay out despite Ghana victory|date=2 December 2022|access-date=18 January 2024|publisher=FIFA}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, Bentancur was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
A dynamic, hard-working, and tactically versatile midfielder, who is comfortable using either foot, Bentancur has been described as a tall and "physically strong" player, who is capable of playing in any midfield position, including as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]], as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]], as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] on either flank, in a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box role]], or even as a [[Midfielder#Mezzala|mezzala]], or as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] behind the forward, due to his ability to make attacking runs from behind.<ref name="Bentancur joins Juventus"/><ref name="Bentancur ha firmato">{{cite web|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/serie-a/juve/2017/04/21-24660790/juventus_bentancur_ha_firmato_fino_al_2022/|title=Juventus, Bentancur ha firmato fino al 2022: "Mi manda Tevez, darò il massimo"|publisher=Il Corriere dello Sport|language=it|date=21 April 2017|access-date=1 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="Calciomercato, ecco chi è Bentancur">{{cite web|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/calcio-mercato/2016/08/11-14273763/calciomercato_ecco_chi_e_bentancur_il_talento_che_piace_a_milan_e_juventus/|title=Calciomercato, ecco chi è Bentancur: il talento che piace a Milan e Juventus|publisher=Il Corriere dello Sport|language=it|author1=Marco Gentile|date=11 August 2016|access-date=1 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="spotlight">{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com.au/football/fifa-world-cup/4/blog/post/3569333/world-cup-scouting-spotlight-moussa-wague-rodrigo-bentancur-mario-fernandes |title=World Cup scouting spotlight: Moussa Wague, Rodrigo Bentancur, Mario Fernandes |publisher=ESPN FC |author1=Matthew Stanger |work=ESPN.com |date=18 July 2018 |access-date=4 April 2019 }}</ref><ref name="teen">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/rodrigo-bentancur-who-arsenal-scouted-boca-teen-who-almost-joined-real-madrid-january |title=Rodrigo Bentancur: Who is the Arsenal-scouted Boca teen who almost joined Real Madrid in January? |magazine=FourFourTwo |author1=Marcus Haydon |date=13 April 2016 |access-date=4 April 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.calciomercato.com/news/juve-matuidi-e-bentancur-hanno-conquistato-tutti-59007|title=Juve, Matuidi e Bentancur hanno conquistato tutti|publisher=calciomercato.com|language=it|date=27 August 2017|access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calciomercato/2017/02/01-20915282/_bentancur_come_pogba_e_la_juventus_scopre_un_vero_duro/|title="Bentancur come Pogba". E la Juventus scopre un vero duro|publisher=Tutto Sport|language=it|author1=Elvira Erbì|date=1 February 2017|access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/calcio/nuove-forze-calcio/11-08-2016/rodrigo-bentancur-pastore-veron-milan-regista-boca-juniors-obiettivo-juventus-real-madrid-160701829958.shtml|title=Bentancur, un po' Pastore un po' Veron: il Milan vuole il regista del Boca Juniors|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|author1=Martin Mazur|date=12 August 2016|access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/juventus-roma-le-pagelle-di-cm-47930 |title=Juve-Roma, le pagelle di CM: Ronaldo onnipotente, Rabiot in crescita. Flop Florenzi e Cristante |publisher=calciomercato.com |language=it |last1=Balice |first1=Nicola |date=22 January 2020 |access-date=30 January 2020 }}</ref>

He also possesses good close control, technique, and quick footwork, which enable him to get past opponents when in possession, while his vision, intelligence, personality, and incisive passing also allow him to set the tempo of his team's play in a more [[Playmaker|creative role]] as a [[Midfielder#Deep-lying playmaker (Strolling 10)|''regista'' deep in midfield]], and create goalscoring opportunities for his teammates after winning back the ball.<ref name="Bentancur ha firmato" /><ref name="Calciomercato, ecco chi è Bentancur" /><ref name="spotlight" /><ref name="teen" /><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Serie-A/Juventus/20-09-2017/juventus-bentancur-gioiello-posso-crescere-ancora-molto-220733482907.shtml|title=Juventus, Bentancur è un gioiello: "E posso crescere ancora molto..."|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=it|author1=Jacopo Gerna|date=21 September 2017|access-date=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://it.eurosport.com/calcio/serie-a/2016-2017/bentancur-parla-gia-da-juventino-visite-mediche-presto.-ma-ora-penso-a-chiudere-bene-col-boca_sto6104955/story.shtml|title=Bentancur parla già da juventino: "Visite mediche presto. Ma ora penso a chiudere bene col Boca"|publisher=Eurosport.com|language=it|author1=Jacopo Fossanova|date=24 March 2017|access-date=27 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football-italia.net/153474/problem-pjanic |title=The problem with Pjanic |publisher=Football Italia |last1=Caferoglu |first1=Livio |date=21 May 2020 |access-date=17 June 2020 }}</ref> His height and strong frame also enable him to act as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|"target man"]] in an advanced midfield role;<ref name="spotlight" /> he has even played as a [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]] on occasion.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/foto/calcio/serie-a/juventus/2017/09/26-31328227/juventus_bentancur_talento_universale_10_giocatori_a_cui_stato_accostato/ |title=Juventus, Bentancur talento universale: 10 giocatori a cui è stato accostato |work=Tutto Sport |language=it |date=26 September 2017 |access-date=26 October 2019 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Bentancur is currently in a long-term relationship with Melany La Banca, an Argentine-Uruguayan from [[Quilmes]], since 2015.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 July 2020 |title=Chi è Melany La Blanca? La compagna di Rodrigo Bentancur |url=https://www.bigodino.it/spettacolo/chi-e-melany-la-blanca-conosciamo-meglio-la-fidanzata-di-rodrigo-bentancur.html |access-date=2023-12-01 |website=Bigodino |language=it-IT}}</ref> They have a daughter.

